<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=10235631681996></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f10235631681996><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10235631681996>RE: stien of moggok</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=10235631681996#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=43653><span id=Scholar>GLASS</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>161 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Jun 8th 3:14 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.41]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>The best way to do this quest as a wizard is to find an enchanter to do it for you.&nbsp;&nbsp;=P<br><br>Seriously, though, I've been over this with other people and have yet to find another class that can pull it off.  The reason is you have to have good faction with so many different groups across Norrath to do the quest.  Here's what I mean:<br><br>1)You have to be able to get deep into Oggok.  Invis works fine, until you have to turn the compendium in to Clurg who, as a merchant, won't be KOS but if your faction with him isn't high enough you will get jack squat from him when you turn in the compendium.  Also, the guards that stand in his bar will be KOS to you.<br><br>2)You have to be at least indifferent with the Halflings in order to get the honey jum.<br><br>3)For the Koalindl fish, you can do it three different ways, the first two I don't recommend.  First, you can kill the fish yourself in Qeynos and loot his corpse.  The pallys and clerics in Qeynos will hate you quickly if you do this.  And since, like you said, you play on FV server, you cannot make a mule to kill the fish for you.<br><br>Secondly, you can kill 'Frostbite', a pet dog in WK who sometimes drops the fish.  This will make you KOS with a bunch of Barbarians, including one who frequents the bar in Freeport where you have to go to get the compendium.<br><br>Third, you can do the Regurgatonic quest, which is the way I recommend, although it's long.  It also requires good faction with the druid guild in Qeynos Hills, and the gnome who gives you the regurgatonic in Ak'anon.<br><br>Lastly, you have to have good enough faction with Gregor, who is the bartender who gives you the compendium.  Here again, if your faction is not high enough, he won't give you anything in return for the four items when you turn them in.<br><br>So, as you can see, it would take some serious time and faction work just to enable you to do the quest.  Much easier to either team up with an Enchanter (when you are high enough to port him/her around you have way more leverage for this option) or just buy one from an enchanter.  They don't go for more than 100-150p these days I believe, although the younger economy on FV may warrant a higher price.<br><br>Have fun,<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
