	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 4th 5:21 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bhert,<br><br>Especially in the beginning, I would not take on several MOB’s deliberately.&nbsp;&nbsp;AoE tend to do a little bit of damage to several people.  If you don’t kill them (which you will not do at lower level), you will be attacked by several MOB’s at the same time.  As a caster, hits on us usually interrupt our spells.  Also as a caster, your weapons and armor choices are limited.  You would be killed in no time.<br><br>Instead, hide behind tanks, in a group, and snipe from a distance.  Do not anger, or aggro, the MOB by hitting it too often. Or else it will leave the tank and run after you.<br><br>Solo, I prefer wide open areas.  See a lone MOB and hit it several times from a distance.  Once you get Root, this is easier.  By the time the MOB gets to melee, it should be under 25%, if not 10%, HP.<br><br>I only use AoE spells when the tank has several MOB’s on him and I time it so I never hit them too often. <br><br>The beginning of a wizard’s career is dangerous, but once you see a few hundred point blasts, you will appreciate it.  Just don’t be too daring at first. <br><br>Tibayn<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Larrymichaelson = 30th Human Wizard<br>Tibayn = 28th Vah Sir Beastlord<br>Haarbinjer = 4th Erud Necro</td></tr>
