	   <tr><td colspan=2>Bhert.<br><br>There is no reason not to play a wizard, but if you want to, maybe a shaman or cleric would be good.&nbsp;&nbsp;They have spells, so you will get the hang of that, but are tough enough that you can hold your own in melee.  I like Vah Shir, but any race can work.  Have fun with it.<br><br>A good, non-human, would be a good wizard, such as high elves or gnomes.  I made a human at first (as all my friends where from Freeport), but the intelligence is a little low.  It is not impossible, so if you want a human, that is ok.  Dark elves and Erudites are great wizards, but they are not well liked, which might be tough at first.<br><br>Stats are raised by items and buff spells.<br><br>As far as skills, I save a lot of them.  Put a little into your favorite weapon (1HB or 2HB are my favorites), put 1 or two into each magic skill (evocation ,etc), put one into sense heading, put one into a trade skill.  I like tailoring.  As a caster, only cloth armors are allowed, so you can make your own.  And, a lot of monsters drop things you can tailor (hides, pelts, silk, etc).  After one or two points, just practice.  Waste an hour or two just casting spells over and over to increase them to a decent level.<br><br>That should get you started for a while.  Don’t worry about specialization for a bit.<br><br>Tibayn<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Larrymichaelson = 30th Human Wizard<br>Tibayn = 28th Vah Sir Beastlord<br>Haarbinjer = 4th Erud Necro</td></tr>
