	   <tr><td colspan=2>I don't think there is a &quot;best&quot; choice.&nbsp;&nbsp;Erudites are not liked by most of the world, so selling loot is an issue.  But they have the most raw mana to keep casting.  Earlier on that might matter.  Later, on, I can buy a few +int items and the gap narrows.  All have pros and cons.  Play whichever one best suits you.  If you are arrogant, the erudite is for you.  Evil; go for dark elf.  Jack of all trades; human.  Etc.<br><br>An elf or gnome seem to be a good compromise of being a good race and having good intelligence. <br>&nbsp;<br>Larrymichaelson = 30th Human Wizard<br>Tibayn = 28th Vah Sir Beastlord<br>Haarbinjer = 4th Erud Necro</td></tr>
