	   <tr><td colspan=2>First of all, good answer Flaxus.&nbsp;&nbsp;I agree with it all.<br><br>Secondly, I don't play a wizard as my main, but I do have one (very young still but I have plans for him).  My main is a 42 Enchanter, which although he is still a bit younger than a 59 or a 55, I feel I have a decent grasp on what is to come in the higher levels.<br><br>&quot;If you like being alone or being used.&quot;<br>Heck, most classes could probably say that from time to time.  Let's face it, in a game where the goal is to get your character to the highest possible level, people are going to use other people to help them achieve the goal.  There are also going to be times where you can shout til your throat gets raw for a group and nobody will ever answer.  I'll admit that I deal with this problem far less than many classes being an enchanter, but I've been there.<br><br>Personally, I love picking up the stray wizard when I can.  The nukes save healer mana.  The evac saves everyone's @$$e$.  And they are generally a pretty agreeable folk.  Also, like Flaxus said, snares and stuns (especially stuns if you ask me) become pretty damn valuable in certain situations.<br><br>One thing that Flaxus didn't touch on that bears mentioning is AoE groups.  Wizards are number one for damage output there as well.<br><br>Not to mentions they are one of only two classes that can be almost anywhere in Norrath (or Luclin for that matter) within 20 minutes or so.<br><br>There will always be people playing the game who will stick to their narrow, preconceived notions of certain classes.  Be glad when they won't group with you, because trust me, after about 30 minutes you will not want to group with them.<br><br>Have fun,<br><br>-Yizz<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
