	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think it goes for most classes, that you can paint a dark painting or a bright painting that illustrates your live in Norrath. The truth is as usual somewhere in between.<br><br>My main is a lvl 55 wizzy. I can take him to Sebilis and get a pickup group if I want to. I may not get it right away but I will get it sooner or later.<br><br>Wizards’ role in groups changes from mid game to the end game. I regard my wizard’s stuns as just as important as the nukes in many groups. The main reason for many of the invites to pickup groups that my wizard gets is that he is able to snare and to cast an intra zone evac, even though the wizards still are the masters of nuking.<br><br>I really like the choice that my wizard has. He is fine both in groups and when I decide to let him solo. I have not gone from level 1 to level 55 without making friends in Norrath. I find myself in a group with friends quite often, who never doubts that group can benefit from the presents of a wizard.<br> <br>I guess that the lack of knowledge about a class is quite often the reason that you see a class described as useless in groups. Don’t let those discussions scare you from picking a class that you would like to play.<br><br>My answer to your question is definately: Yes, they are worth it<br><br>Regards,<br>Flaxus, 55 wizard<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
