	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Currently lvl 46 Wizard that thought I'd pass down some of the things that have worked for me, these are mainly solo alternatives since that's the way I have gone about things a lot of the time.<br>Someone said start of in Misty Thicket... Dunno of this is the best spot, but that's what I did and it worked fine.<br>Lvl 20: Lake Rathe Tear. Follow right wall when you enter from Karanas and you'll find 2 spawn towers, just outside Arena. Great xp, zone nearby, think the birdies even droped some runes I needed. Bind here and gate out and sell when you're full.<br><br>Lvl 30: Crystal Caverns. Now this may not be totally legit to some, but explore the first icy cave you get to heading towards orcs from town and you'll find a very usefull pathing thing that can and will save your life. This is basically also the thing that makes this place soloable at this level. Downtime will be pretty high, but the xp is well worth the effort.<br><br>Lvl 38: (or so) Soloed Frost Giant Scouts in GD. Right at the zone to EW is a good spot. This way you can make a run for it if you must. These guys are probably the poorest Giants around though, so don't expect to get rich. They do however drop heads, toes, helms etc... that you can sell to other players or use yourself for SS faction quests, Coldain Shawl Quest etc. Also, velium drops are pretty common so you should be able to raise some money. Bring a WR bag though.<br><br>Lvl 40: (again... or so) Quad kiting Ulthorks in EW. This raises Incredible amounts of xp and decent loot too if you get lucky. To make this as safe and effective as possible I'd suggest trying to get the Staff of Temporate Flux Quest done, if you haven't already (great for pulling on the move) and you will also need either plenty of SOW charges or Jboots (Which you should break your neck to get anyway, they are a soloing Wizards best friend every day)<br>As a footnote... Save all the Ulthork tusks you find. Gate to CS and try not to get killed while you're there :) Anyway, donw my the water is where the Othmir hang out, and the chief there will give you a randmo gem or jewelry piece for every 4 tusks you turn in. Usually sells for a little over 100pp and can be worth it.<br><br>Now at 46 Ulthorks aren't that good xp no more, have stuck around killing some Ulthork Men o War though. Xp not that good since I can only do 1 at a time, but apparently they drop spells, very&nbsp;&nbsp;rarely, but still. If you are the kinda guy that sell instead of give loot spells away you can probably make some cash.<br><br>Time to find new huntinggrounds now though.. So if anyone have a good suggestion plz respond to this. Only preqequisites I have is that I want a soloable spot that does not ruin Coldain or CoV faction.<br><br>Thanks and good luck my fellow wizards.<br><br>/Thantaroz Ccezanth, 46 seasons Wizard of Zeb. <br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed May 15 10:46:43 2002</em><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
