<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102086849776229></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102086849776229><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=102086849776229>RE: HELP WITH 12TH WIZZARD</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=102086849776229#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=84230><span id= >XiththeWizard</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>9 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 8th 10:42 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Intel does nothing for your effectiveness in groups, all it does is increase your total manapool.&nbsp;&nbsp;Once you cast that first spell your effectiveness is the same as a wizard with top end gear/stats.  All wizards meditate the same (unless your increadably lucky and have a flowing thought item) and that is what counts.  After casting that first nuke, you regain mana the same as any other wizard.  The higher manapool is only noticable in the first 10 seconds of combat, where the wizard with more mana can toss one or 2 more nukes before oom.  Once you start the sit, stand, nuke cycle, your just as well off as anyone else.  I wouldnt bring yourself down because you have a little lower intel than others, because you regain mana at the same rate, and in a group, you should never be Full Mana, if you are, means your group isnt performing fast enough, or you went AFK for a few minutes.  Mana regeneration is what you should be looking at, not total mana, and regeneration is the same for everyone.  And as your levels increase, youll be earning more money, and with that more money, you can buy more intel gear.  With the amount of intel gear on the market now, when you get a little higher, you should have no problems getting your intel up to where you feel comfortable.<br><br>Baron Xith N'Shezbenon<br>Sorcerer, Dark Templars<br>Lvl 60 Wizard.<br>Founder of Team KS<br>Class Leader<br>Xegony<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
