	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Don't worry too much about it.&nbsp;&nbsp;When I built my wizard, I followed some bad advice and put about 8 points on WISDOM!  (At the time, a lot of people were under the mistaken impression that wisdom would help prevent spell fizzling!)  This turns out to do NOTHING for me.  <br><br>But, you know what?  It DOESN'T matter!  I made up the int points with one or two purchased +int items and went on my way.  (Actually, I camped Cubert a while and got my earrings, and got a good deal on Rose Quartz rings.  Eventually I did the Kolindi fish thing to improve the finger slots.) In the end, it matters a whole lot more how well you play your charactor, than what his base stats are -- you can find items to adjust your stats as you progress, but you won't progress at all if you don't learn how to play your wiz!<br><br>Read through these posts, and look at some of the wizard only websites. (Graffe's comes to mind.)  The most important thing to learn is how to play your wiz in a group, which is TOTALLY DIFFERENT than how you play him when you solo!  The biggest difference is that when you are in a group you want to conserve your mana and make sure your nukes land when they are most effective. And MED, MED, MED -- don't EVER let your self go OOM and if you do, don't tell anyone =) -- you are useless to your group if you let this happen.<br><br>When you solo, you have to do just about the opposite--hurry up and get as many nukes off as you can!  Also when you solo--especially at lower levels, don't take on anything above a blue! (and even them you gotta watch)  Life is just like that for us until we grow up a bit!<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>--Alikaar of Tarrew Mar<br></td></tr>
