<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102055419246969></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102055419246969><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=102055419246969>RE: HELP WITH 12TH WIZZARD</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=102055419246969#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=142500><span id= >Flaxus</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, May 4th 7:24 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>My wizard has been grouping with people many many times and I have never met anyone, who asked me about any of my stats before they decided if they wanted to group with me. Furthermore I find it unlikely to believe that a single stat has saved my group in many situations.<br><br>I don’t think you need to worry too much about your INT if you don’t want to. I would suggest focusing on learning the strengths and the weaknesses of the class you have chosen. It is impossible for you to raise your INT significantly at your level if you don’t have a huge pile of platinum pieces anyway. Sure you can raise it a little by doing quests. I would recommend checking out the quest involving Kubert in Qeynos Catacombs, if your character is in that end of Norrath. Kubert quest is easy at your level and results in some +3 INT earrings. You can check out <a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=456" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=456</a> for more information.<br><br>At level 1 a wizard’s offensive strength is piercing with a sharp little knife. There is no problem to do so when you solo.<br><br>At level 12 wizards’ offensive strength is nuking (with both single target AND area based spells). It’s hard to nuke when you solo at level 12, because mobs will interrupt your spell casting by beating you up. It’s much easier to nuke when you are grouped.&nbsp;&nbsp; <br><br>This changes a bit when you reach level 29. In level 29 you get two very important spells. You get the first snare spell and the first porting spells. Porting spells can make you able to afford sow potions. Sow poitons and snare will make you able to keep distance to the mobs while you nuke them, without having a group. This is referred to as kiting, but I am getting away from topic as your concern is about advancing from level 12.<br><br>I am afraid that making a new little wizard from scratch is your only realistic option if you insist to raise your INT a lot right now, but I don’t think it is necassery to do it if you don’t want to. <br><br>I was always poor at lower levels. I had money to spent on food and spells and not much more than that. Most INT items will be beyond your reach if you are in a similar situation. Look for mana items if you do happen to get money to spend. I am convinced that a level 12 wizard will be able to cast more nukes per spend Platinum Piece when the money is spend on mana items instead of INT items (&lt;- I hope you can see what I mean by that).<br><br>My conclusion is that you should try to find groups. Look for groups in areas with mobs, which are harder than the ones that you can (or almost can) solo. Picking as high-level mobs as possible is important in order to level efficently, not necasserly in order to have an enjoyable afternoon.<br><br>Kind Regards,<br>Flaxus (Level 55 wizard)<br><br>PS: Another thing worth considering is that there are many fine human wizards in Norrath and not one of them can possibly have more than 110 INT before they start adding items or buffs.<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
