	   <tr><td colspan=2>Part of the reason for dumping all your points into INT is because INT increasing items are generally more expensive and more difficult to find (good ones anyway).&nbsp;&nbsp;Especially once you start looking for and pricing INT armor items (like sleeves, shoes, etc.) you'll see what I mean.  For anything past +5INT the going starts getting REALLY tough, and it's not so easy for wizzies to get into groups (let's hope caster balancing fixes some of those woes).<br><br>That said, you may well want to start a new character.  If not, here are some decent INT lower level items you can obtain fairly easily:<br>- Band of Rodcet Nife (Lore Item)<br>- Stein of Moggok (this is generally thought of as an enchanter quest; these sell for about 800pp but it's also +10INT which is positively indispensable if you asked me)<br>- Students Homework (Ranged, drops in ToFS)<br>- Ancient Sensate Eye (+4INT from PC; I don't see this one for sale very often, but you will probably not have trouble getting a guildie to camp the Reishicyben for you, since he drops some other decent loot as well)<br>- Gatorscale Sleeves<br>- Golden Ear Stud (Cubert quest in Qeynos)<br><br>These are just a few that I can think of off the top of my head.  Once you hit 20th or so, start planning where you're going to hunt with the locations of the wizard rods for your Staff of the Wheel.  Whenever you happen to be near one grab it.<br><br>Good luck!<br><br>Lhiannon<br>34th season wizard<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
