	   <tr><td colspan=2>To me who is used to play a caster, it is funny to see you regard it as an AC penalty when your AGI is below 75. I myself regard it as a AC bonus when my AGI is above 75 - but the point is that I agree: 5 points in agi will be well used. Better AC will help you casting spells without being interrupted. <br><br>20 int is a classic way to spent the majority of the point, I dont think you will regret that either.<br><br>The most important influence of stamania is the influence it has on your number of hitpoints. The number of hit points will become more or less irrelevant later in the game and having spent the points in AGI, just might make up for a few hitpoints. I dont think thats where you want to spent your points.<br><br>Another popular option is to put the points into strength for the obvious reason that it will let you carry more. I dont think thats the best choice, considering that strength items are easy to get and that you are used to play a monk who cannot carry much either.<br><br>So my advice is to put 5 points in AGI and 20 in INT, when you create an Eruidte Wizard. Focus on manaitems and perhaps strength items if you are going to twink your little wizzie a little.<br><br>Hope my comment is of some use to you. <br><br>Good luck !<br><br>Regards,<br>Flaxus lvl 54 wiz<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
