<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=102027467712769></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f102027467712769><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=102027467712769>RE: Equipment</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=102027467712769#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=93845><span id=Guru>Arjaizen</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>173 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, May 1st 1:45 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.81]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Here's a few suggestions that won't cost any of the plat you're willing to spend.:<br><br>Gorge of King Xorbb (aka, the Beholder's Maze): <br>Camp the evil eyes.&nbsp;&nbsp;They will occasionally drop polished bone bracelets that give +3 to INT and WIS.  Doable solo if your main is high 20's or better.<br><br>The Warrens:<br>Camp the Cave Bat Lord.  He drops Azzar's Deadly Hat, which can be turned in to Azzar Habib (Upstairs in the structure at that leads into the Paineel newbie area.)  Azzar will give you the Black Lace Sash, which will add +2 to INT, DEX, and AGI.  Note that you need good faction with Heretics to do this.  You get that by killing LOTS of kobolds in the Warrens.  If your faction is good, you can solo the Cave Bat Lord in your low 20's<br><br>Also in the Warrens, you can get the Cloak of the Forlorn, which drops off Prince Gragnor.  The Cloak is +3 INT, +5 mana, -3 WIS, and +1 MR.  The Prince CAN be soloed by low 20's but it's safer to wait until mid to upper 20's, so you don't draw any of his friends into the fray.<br><br>While the sash may require a lot more time than you're willing to spend (since it takes quite a while to build faction,) The bracelets should be realtively easy.  I got two in a couple of hours.  The robe is more iffy, as the Prince has a number of special drops, and it's a crapshoot which you get.<br><br>Good luck.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>Arjaizen Izrhume<br>37th Circle Wizard of Erudin<br>Fallen Wolves</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
